      • launchCommand

        private int launchCommand(java.lang.String[] userCommand)
        The function takes a String array as an argument, and checks the first element of the array. If the first element is empty, the function does nothing. If the first element is "help", the function checks if the second element is empty. If it is, the function prints the help message for the command "help". If it is not empty, the function checks if the command exists. If it does, the function prints the help message for the command. If it does not, the function prints the message "No such command". If the first element is "info", the function checks if the second element is empty. If it is, the function prints the info message for the command "info". If it is not empty, the function checks if the command exists. If it does, the function prints the info message for the command. If it does not, the function prints the message "No such command".         Parameters:
        userCommand - the command entered by the user
        Returns:
        The return value is an integer that is either 0, 1, or 2.
